">\n\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t<div id=\"siteNotice\" class=\"mw-body-content\"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n\t</div>\n\t<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Stephen Bellesini</h1>\n\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub2\"></div>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#searchInput\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"n\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:gold;\"><div style=\"display:inline;\" class=\"fn\">Blessed Stephen Bellesini</div></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Beato Stefano Bellesini.JPG\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG/250px-Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"250\" height=\"188\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG/375px-Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG/500px-Beato_Stefano_Bellesini.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"4320\" data-file-height=\"3240\" /></a><div>Reliquary of Stephen Bellesini</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>November 25, 1774<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Trento\" title=\"Trento\">Trento</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Italy\" title=\"Italy\">Italy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>February 2, 1840<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Genazzano,_Italy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Genazzano, Italy\">Genazzano</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Italy\" title=\"Italy\">Italy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Venerated&#160;in</th><td><a href=\"/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Church\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Roman Catholic Church\">Roman Catholic Church</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Beatification\" title=\"Beatification\">Beatified</a></th><td>December 27, 1904, <a href=\"/wiki/Vatican_City\" title=\"Vatican City\">Vatican City</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Pope_Pius_X\" title=\"Pope Pius X\">Pope Pius X</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"nowrap\">Major <a href=\"/wiki/Shrine\" title=\"Shrine\">shrine</a></span></th><td>\"Westcourt\", Callan, Ireland; International Heritage Centre, \"Mount Sion\", Waterford, Ireland</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Calendar_of_saints\" title=\"Calendar of saints\">Feast</a></th><td>February 3</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Blessed <b>Stephen Bellesini</b> was a <a href=\"/wiki/Friar\" title=\"Friar\">friar</a> in the Order of the <a href=\"/wiki/Hermits_of_St_Augustine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hermits of St Augustine\">Hermits of St Augustine</a> (OSA), who was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Trento\" title=\"Trento\">Trento</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Italy\" title=\"Italy\">Italy</a>, on November 25, 1774, and died in <a href=\"/wiki/Genazzano,_Italy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Genazzano, Italy\">Genazzano, Italy</a>, on February 2, 1840.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stephen_Bellesini&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Of the Italian aristocracy, Luigi Giuseppe Bellesini joined the Augustinians in 1790, taking the name Stefano, and made his profession on May 31, 1794. After studies in Rome and Bologna, he was forced to return to Trento during the government suppression of religious houses and completed his theological education there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-osa_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-osa-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Bellesini was ordained in 1797 and served primarily as a preacher and rector of the small chapel attached to the Order\u2019s monastery in Trento.<sup id=\"cite_ref-west_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-west-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1810 the monastery in Trento was also ordered closed and Bellesini went to live at his brother's house where he lived as a secular priest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-west_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-west-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He dedicated his time to teaching poor children of the city. He also gave food, clothing and encouragement to his students. Bellesini became a great champion of the education of youth and the local authorities appointed him Director and Superintendent of all schools in the district.<sup id=\"cite_ref-osa_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-osa-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In September 1817 he resigned from these offices and made his way to Rome in order to resume his religious life.<sup id=\"cite_ref-osa_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-osa-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The reaction in Trento was first shock, then indignation, and finally condemnation. The same government that had valued his work so highly now proclaimed him to be an exile and forbade him to return under threat of punishment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-villanova_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-villanova-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> For a period, he was Novice Master for his Order, and in 1825 was transferred to Genazzano, home to the miraculous fresco of <a href=\"/wiki/Our_Lady_of_Good_Counsel\" title=\"Our Lady of Good Counsel\">Our Lady of Good Counsel</a>, for whom he had a great devotion. He was named parish priest in 1831.<sup id=\"cite_ref-west_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-west-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>During a <a href=\"/wiki/Cholera\" title=\"Cholera\">cholera</a> epidemic in January 1840, while answering a call to care for a sick parishioner, he tripped and fell. A cut on his leg became infected, and he developed a high fever. He tried to remain active for the next two days, but the fever never went away. He died February 2, 1840 in Genazzano. His remains are at the Shrine of Our Mother of Good Counsel in Genazzano.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Veneration\">Veneration</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stephen_Bellesini&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Veneration\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He was beatified by Pope <a href=\"/wiki/Pius_X\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pius X\">Pius X</a>, on December 27, 1904, and his Feast Day is February 3.\n</p><p>In Massachusetts is found the Blessed Stephen Bellesini OSA Academy, in collaboration with <a href=\"/wiki/Merrimack_College\" title=\"Merrimack College\">Merrimack College</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stephen_Bellesini&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-osa-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-osa_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-osa_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-osa_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://augustinians.net/index.php?page=bellesini_en\">\"Blessed Stephen Bellesini, priest\", Order of Saint Augustine</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-west-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-west_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-west_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-west_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://osa-west.org/blessedstephenbellesini.html\">\"Blessed Stephen Bellesini\", Augustinians of the Western United States</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-villanova-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-villanova_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www1.villanova.edu/villanova/mission/campusministry/spirituality/resources/spirituality/augustinians/saints/stephen.html\">\"St. Stephen Bellesini\", Villanova University</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://midwestaugustinians.org/bl-stephen-bellesini\">\"Bl. Stephen Bellesini\", Midwest Augustinians</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<ul><li><i>New Catholic Encyclopedia</i>, The Catholic University of America, 1967.</li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox authority-control\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q1668199&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th id=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_